Shell Programming Notes - 2

Environment Variables

Naming Convention:
User Defined Variables - Lower Case Letter
System Defined Variables - Upper Case Letter

env command is used to list all the environment variables.

User Defined Environment Variables

Shell Variables (bash)
projdir = /home/km/KM_GITHUB
ls -la $projdir; cd $projdir

Environment Variables (bash)
cd $HOME
export DEBUG=1
./find_extraterrestial_life
(displays debug information if DEBUG is set)

Creating a user defined variable
export <variable_name> = <variable_value>
export projdir=/home/km/KM_GITHUB
echo $projdir -> Prints the Project Directory defined to the variable.

System Defined Environment Variables
LD_LIBRARY_PATH
MANPATH
PATH
PRINTER
SHELL
USER
HOSTNAME
HOME
EDITOR
DISPLAY

Using System Defined User Variable
echo $USER


alias -> Command Shortcut
alias ls = 'ls -la
alias rm = 'rm -ri'

